where Y is the crop yield; X is the application rate of N, P2O5, or K2O fertilizer; s0 is the equivalent of soil supplying nutrient; c is the yield coefficient of fertilization; and A is the conversion coefficient of soil fertility to rice yield at X = 0, which comprehensively reflects the soil productivity. Therefore, a TNFM can be described according to the principle of irreplaceable function of plant nutrient elements as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
